import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['budgetYear'])]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='value', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['value'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {data["value"].median():.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Budget Value')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of budget values?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['budgetYear'])]
    data = data[pd.notna(data['forecastYear'])]
    sns.set_style("darkgrid")
    sns.lineplot(x="budgetYear", y="value", data=data, label="Budget")
    sns.lineplot(x="forecastYear", y="value", data=data, label="Forecast")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel("Year")
    plt.ylabel("Value")
    plt.title("How do the budget and forecast values compare over time?")
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='abs_diff', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['abs_diff'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['abs_diff'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('Absolute Difference between Budget and Forecast Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of absolute difference between budget and forecast values?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
